11/11/21, 1:50 PM - Baggha: *To:* 
director@iitbhu.ac.in

 *CC:* 
doaa@iitbhu.ac.in
dosa@iitbhu.ac.in
dora@iitbhu.ac.in
dofa@iitbhu.ac.in
registrar@iitbhu.ac.in
adoaa_ug@iitbhu.ac.in

*Content* - 
Dear Sir,
It is sad to inform you that the efforts by the administration in calling back the students to the campus have been disheartening. One of the significant setbacks in all of this is the communication gap between students and administration. We must bridge this gap with regular emails with updates from your side and the student's parliament.
We, as students, insist you give us a proper plan regarding the college reopening. Calling back the 5th year students have taken more than 20 days (still counting), and they are only 200 in number; if this pace is followed, how calling back around 4800 students in December is possible. We need to be informed well in advance so that the students who live far away can book the tickets.
Unfortunately, we feel that doing next sem offline is yet another fake promise to shut us down from creating chaos, move on with our end semester examination quietly and start another online semester.  
We understand all your worries and the importance of the guidelines provided by the government, but it is time for us to take the next step forward. Many IIT, NIT and other institutes across India have reopened, they have even allowed sharing of rooms, so we can follow the guidelines to the extent they are following.
We have seen the pictures of Deepotsav, Chhath and many more being celebrated on the campus right now. It is devastating that everyone is allowed on the campus except us; the excuse that our campus is an open campus should not be given.
About sharing of rooms, we know that it is not possible to allot single-seater for everyone, hence sharing of rooms should be started, without giving some inappropriate reasons.
We insist you give us the exact dates of all the UG's when the administration plans to call them back to the campus. Please inform this before the 20th of November. We will not stop putting our efforts until our demands are fulfilled. Lack of proper intimation from the administration side is making us vulnerable and restless.  

We are hoping for an immediate reply with the dates of reopening.
Thanks and regards

Many IIT, NIT and other institutes across India have reopened, they have even allowed sharing of rooms, so we can follow the guidelines to the extent they are following.
We have seen the pictures of Deepotsav, Chhath and many more being celebrated on the campus right now. It is devastating that everyone is allowed on the campus except us; the excuse that our campus is an open campus should not be given.

*Content* - 
Dear Sir,
It is sad to inform you that the efforts by the administration in calling back the students to the campus have been disheartening. One of the significant setbacks in all of this is the communication gap between students and administration. We must bridge this gap with regular emails with updates from your side and the student's parliament.
We, as students, insist you give us a proper plan regarding the college reopening. Calling back the 5th year students have taken more than 20 days (still counting), and they are only 200 in number; if this pace is followed, how calling back around 4800 students in December is possible. We need to be informed well in advance so that the students who live far away can book the tickets.
Unfortunately, we feel that doing next sem offline is yet another fake promise to shut us down from creating chaos, move on with our end semester examination quietly and start another online semester.  
We understand all your worries and the importance of the guidelines provided by the government, but it is time for us to take the next step forward. Many IIT, NIT and other institutes across India have reopened, they have even allowed sharing of rooms, so we can follow the guidelines to the extent they are following.
We have seen the pictures of Deepotsav, Chhath and many more being celebrated on the campus right now. It is devastating that everyone is allowed on the campus except us; the excuse that our campus is an open campus should not be given.
About sharing of rooms, we know that it is not possible to allot single-seater for everyone, hence sharing of rooms should be started, without giving some inappropriate reasons.
*We insist you give us the exact dates of all the UG's when the administration plans to call them back to the campus and call 4th yr Resource Constrained students sitting for placements on an immediate basis, they should be called by 20thNov* . Please inform this *before the 20th of November*. We will not stop putting our efforts until our demands are fulfilled. Lack of proper intimation from the administration side is making us vulnerable and restless.  

We are hoping for an immediate reply with the dates of reopening.
Thanks and regards

Kashiyatra, the annual socio-cultural fest of IIT(BHU) Varanasi, is known to witness numerous artists flying worldwide and becomes home for participants from throughout the country.

We are looking to recruit dedicated and zealous candidates to make Kashiyatra more memorable as it has always been. Positions are available in the following teams :

Publicity Team
Marketing Team
Public Relations Team
Operations and Logistics Team
Events Team
Creative Design Team
Content Team


Want to be part of such an esteemed fest? Fill in the google form attached, and we'll get in touch with you soon.

Deadline: Sunday, 20th November 2021, 23:59

11/18/21, 3:08 PM - Baggha: As planned before, we are now going to post on Facebook and bring our issues to the attention of the Administration publicly.

Below is the content to be posted on Facebook.

We request all of you to post this yourself, get it posted by your friends and other pages on Facebook.

Tag the IIT (BHU) page and other administration members.
11/18/21, 3:08 PM - Baggha: A reminder to the IIT (BHU) administration: education with just classes and assignments will surely be enough for a degree but not enough to make quality engineers. College life is necessary for the overall growth of students!

Almost all IITs have started calling their students back or have given a concrete plan with dates. Only IIT (BHU) is keeping its students in the dark, gobbling up the 1 lakh per sem fees.

Despite repeated student efforts, there is no clarity of the Re-opening Schedule given by the admin of IIT (BHU). We have been home for the last 2 years, and it's high time to call us back to campus! Students will need sufficient time to book tickets, plan their journey, so admin should inform the students about the exact dates and re-opening plan well in advanced.

We have the following demand for the administration:
1. We want the exact dates for calling the students (4, 3, 2 years) back to campus as well as float the willingness form and plan the arrival for 2/3 years as soon as possible.
2. If the admin plans to call all students at once, then how and when will that happen?
3. Other IITs/NITs have allowed double accommodation, even those whose room sizes are the same as our college. The administration should explore possible of sharing room wherever required. 
4. We want a mail of detailed plan before end sems.

We hope the administration cooperates with the students and works towards college re-opening.

12/20/21, 11:23 AM - Aditya Kulkarni: Respected Sir, 
With due respect and humble submission, we would like to bring the following pain points to your kind notice and demand immediate action on the same. 

It's been a week since we were clued up to be ready for arriving in the campus and that necessary arrangements are being made to call the UGs of 2nd and 3rd year to the campus. I would like to bring the following issues to your kind notice : 

1- There was a mention about the institute needing some time to prepare the plan to call the UGs to the campus. There wasn't any concrete mention of the duration required for the same. 
2- There wasn't any mention about the amount of time UGs will be given to pad up for the travel and other necessary preparations while coming to the campus. I would also mention that students living in different parts of the country would need prior notice so that they can make necessary arrangements. 
3- As per previously mentioned tentative dates, we were about to reach the campus in the first week of January. It's Christmas and New year and the unavailability of tickets is a big issue. The UGs who had already booked their tickets fearing unavailability during peak time faced huge losses on account of arrival dates not being concrete. 
4- No information about accommodation at the college has been mentioned in the mail sent to the students.
5- Student chaos amidst confusing situations when no dates have been mentioned and that the even semester is almost up for a start. 

For the above mentioned problems, we would request the following actions to be taken immediately: 

1- A mail mentioning the exact dates of arrival to the college as soon as possible. 
2- List of hostels that are available and details about the plan of action that the institute has undertaken. 
3- If not, the institute must tell us how much time it's going to need in order to frame a plan of action. 

These measures, if brought into effect could bring about a wave of assurance and positivity among the undergraduates, thus reducing chaos. It's expected of our administration to take sensible and timely measures to ensure proper facilitation of arrival of students into the college campus.

12/31/21, 2:00 PM - Aditya Kulkarni: Respected Sir,

I hope the administration will be doing well on campus without most students. As per the previous mail sent by the college, the Institute provided the info that the college for 2/3 years (B.Tech + IDD) and 4th year (IDD) will be reopened before starting the new semester.

Even after receiving registration & class dates for the semester, we still have not received any information for the reopening.

In this respect, I want to show you the condition of all other IITs:

1. IIT Patna: all already on the campus
2. IIT Kanpur: dates given from 29-31 December
3. IIT KGP: 29-31 December
4. IIT Bombay: already students can come as per their convenience
5. IIT R: All students already on campus
6. IIT M:  Already called 2nd yearites and going to call 3rd yearites in January
7. IIT D: Mostly students already on campus
8. IIT ISM: dates given from 27 Dec - 1 Jan
9. Nearly all new IITs already opened from 2-3 months

Kanpur, which is nearest to our IIT, has called back 2/3/4+ year students without any phases or batched. Now IIT BHU - called ONLY 30 3rd yearite students, without any info for the remaining students. There is no communication about the next batchh of students, date of coming back to campus or even that the administration is willing to call the students back.

Students have lost the precious 2 years of their college life. Student of 2nd year have not even seen the campus yet, and if this semester also goes by, they'll be in 3rd year, without being to campus even once. You should understand the mental state of students, how bad they feel and how horrifying is the thought of graduating online. 

Noticing the administration's ignorance on this sensitive issue, we students have decided to *boycott ALL academic activities*, including classes, quizzes, and assignments, from the 3rd of January until all students are allowed to come to the campus.

Instead of another mail saying that the administration is working to explore the possibilities, we want exact dates of return for all students, just as the "parent IITs" of IIT (BHU) have done. If not, then expect the reputation of IIT (BHU) to fall even down, which would surely be reflected in NIRF ranking. 

Hence, for everyone's well being, we request you to call back students to campus with immediate effect.

Thanking You,

1/21/22, 4:59 PM - Dev Raj IIT BHU: @918824889498  the stopping criteria of epsilon is always wrt what you need to find,in bisection method we initially have a and b as borders then we know the root is between a b, so error is b - a (as x can be very close to a or very close to b) after 1 iter, interval will be (b-a)/2, n iter (b-a)/2^n .... so (b-a)/2^n <= e, which on rearranging gets you the formula for number of iter

2/10/22, 1:00 PM - Pranav Suresh: Hola IITians, 
Do you want to pursue an MS or a PhD in a foreign country? 

Greetings from the Research Community, IIT (BHU) and the International Exchange Team, Student Counseling Services! In collaboration with Ambitio, we welcome you to an Ask Me Anything session on Higher Education Abroad by Mr Dhiraj Srivastava. He is currently pursuing his Master's in Computer Science at Virginia Tech, USA. This session will give you a clear picture of the life of a Master's student pursuing research in the USA. 

Ambitio provides you with an opportunity to interact with mentors from the Ivy League colleges like Columbia University, Cornell University, Carnegie Mellon University, the University of Pennsylvania for your Master’s applications. Mentors assist in shortlisting target schools, writing SOPs, essays, LORs, and the interview process, so that you get accepted into your dream college. 

Kindly fill out the attached google form if you want to connect to a mentor and get personalized guidance for FREE.
Google form: https://forms.gle/PdXCbLrYaiTaxXpQA 

Date: 12th February, Saturday
Time: 6:00-7:00 PM
Link: https://bit.ly/34nPIFn 

Mark your calendar and get ready for an insightful session.

Thanks and regards,
The Research community, IIT (BHU) and the International Exchange Team, SCS.

2/23/22, 3:26 PM - SD IIT BHU: Respected Sir,

We understand and appreciate the efforts you are making to call us back. We just want to mention a few points here that please call us back irrespective of conditions of the hostel, we are ready to adjust with any condition of hostels. We need only room for accommodation and mess only, nothing else we expect from admins right now.

Secondly, we want to witness technex offline in hybrid mode. To witness a fest while being on campus has become a dream now for many sophomores. Since everything outside is normal. All other colleges have called sophomores back. Even in some colleges freshers have also been called. *IIT Guwahati, MNNIT* have called their students back recently with official dates. All other IITs have their students on campus. We are just requesting you to fasten the process of hostel allocation and call us by 7th March. Also, a fest could reach its height much more easily if the members working for it will be present with each other and coordinate with themselves. We hope we can witness technex in hybrid mode while being on campus and then continue staying in the hostels.

Also if we'll be called after Holi, then we would have less time for everything since we'll need at least one week to settle down, then normal studies and we'll be having endsems in 2 weeks only. So if they'll call us back by the 7th March we'll surely have some cherishing moments of our college life through fest technex and other upcoming events as well.

We hope you'll understand the situation of students who are sitting at home since we have not been to campus for two years.

2/27/22, 5:58 PM - Ayush Gupta: Hey everyone!
 
I'm Ayush Gupta, Mathematics and Computing 2nd Year, a former winter research intern at Changwon National University, South Korea. This message invites students from our batch to apply for the *Summer Research Internship opportunity at Changwon National University, South Korea, under Professor Oh-Seol Kwon.*

This internship is an excellent opportunity for *second-year students*. It introduces you to the research possibilities happening around the globe and publish a paper on your findings under a renowned professor.
Professor Kwon will be collaborating with a professor from Princeton University for this project. So, this internship can also give you an excellent opportunity to work at an Ivy League research university.

I urge everyone interested in the fields of Computer Vision, but not restricted to it, to apply for this opportunity. The internship will be for *~12 weeks (May 2022 to July 2022)* and will be conducted virtually. There will also be international students in the labs who will help you when needed.

In the winter of 2021, 3 students of IIT (BHU) successfully completed their internship. My project during the internship was based on "Super Resolution and Object Detection using Generative Adversarial Nets (GANs) for Autonomous Driving" and the paper is due to be published. My batchmates, Ayush Ishan (met20) worked on "Real time Road Segmentation via FCN based architecture", and Eshaan Agarwal (eee20) worked on "Ensemble based U-Net Algorithm for Real Time Road Semantic Segmentation". Seniors in the past have had projects related to Face Recognition in Low Light Settings, Advanced Driver Assistance Systems, Haze Removal, etc. You can find more info here http://islab.cwnu.ac.kr/interns.htm.

3-4 students from our institute will be offered the internship. The project will be on *XAI-based Deep Learning (object recognition) for Autonomous Driving*. Professor Kwon will select students in mid-March and proceed with the program from May to July. Since it will be conducted online, selected students can start in advance if they wish to do so.

In lieu of the above, interested folks may send their resumes to me via this form: https://forms.gle/81U56FD5Xzk8MALk6

You can check the Professor's website: http://islab.changwon.ac.kr/
Kindly do not contact the Professor personally. Send your resume to me via the Google Form and I will forward it to him.

Apply by 11:59 pm, 4th March 2022 (Friday)

For any queries, you can send me an email (ayush.gupta.mat20@iitbhu.ac.in), or you can contact me through WhatsApp (+91 98997 41300)

Regards
Ayush

3/11/22, 10:59 PM - Aditya Kulkarni: Dear metallurgy walo,
So you asked me few questions regarding the yesterday's mail and all. Here's what I can tell you at this moment (baad me kuch important hoga to I will add on ... Just cheeel ) 

Q1. *Is it compulsory to come ?? And if not, do I need to pay fees ??*
No, it's not compulsory at all. And if you don't come,  don't pay the fees.

Q2. *Hostel fees Rs 5000 why ?*
For hostel fees: You have to pay the required amount.
For Mess charges: You will get your mess refund after end sem


Q3. *Second year PG wale students pehle jakar room me reh sakte ??*
No it's not possible. There are several protocols to be followed when you visit campus for the first time. And for keeping it in well organised manner, it's better that you all come on/after 21st March.

Q4. *Documents needed ??*
(personal opinion - Make a separate File and keep your all demn important documents in it. Since the most of you are not from Uttar Pradesh, it will be better if you carry all important documents. Upload all important PDFs on your institute I'd drive👍)
Atleast bring Class 10,12, Aadhaar Card, Vaccination Certificate, JEE Marksheet, Passport Photos etc.

If you have any other query, pm kar dena whatsapp pe
And maine kuch logo se baat karke hi ye sab likha h so In case kuch change hua to I will inform you. 

~ Aapka Pyaara Vidhayak 😂

3/17/22, 7:54 PM - SD IIT BHU: Hola Sophos!
Congratulations on finally being called to the campus. To give our campus life a great headstart and compensate for the fun that we missed in the 2 years we will be having an INTER BRANCH SPORTS event exclusively for sophomores once everyone arrives!

Events:
• Badminton [Men's Doubles, Women's doubles, Mixed Doubles per division]
• Cricket
• Soccer 
• Kabaddi 

Fill out this form to register for the event: https://forms.gle/ePTrJ4JDDBjggND58

*This event will be only for 2nd yearites. Final dates will be announced soon.*

The aforementioned form is only to get a count of the participants from each branch, interested in the event. Once u arrive at campus it's easy for everyone to make teams of every branch so for now, participant entries count is mandatory because it's easy for scheduling matches. 

Points to remember: 
- Hetero Teams are allowed (mix of boys and girls).
- The last date to fill out the form is 25th March.
- You can take part in any no. of sports, but you are allowed to be in only one team of a particular sport.
 
For more information contact: 
Hitesh Nama 8955460414

3/19/22, 2:34 PM - SD IIT BHU: The program on "SOFT SKILLS" is meant to imbibe professionalism among students for stimulating career growth. The engineers and managers are supposed to work in a team. It is where they need to work with and lead the colleagues. To become successful, one has to understand their role as a leader. One needs to know how to complete the project by fixing the timelines appropriately, structuring the responsibilities, etc. Besides, one has to be good at managing time and team both. 

From the above perspective, it is essential to understand various dimensions of soft skills and make them a part of one's personality. The person possessing such qualities will be one with the right problem-solving and critical thinking skills, the two crucial soft skills listed by World Economic Forum for the year 2022.

Looking in the importance of the soft skills for a better placement and career growth, Round 3 of Soft Skills Program is being organized during Azadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav year. The six sessions will be delivered by our Distinguished Alumnus, Dr. Manu Vora (IIT BHU, CHE'1968) from Chicago, USA. 

*It is desired that you attend all the sessions to obtain a program participation certificate. This certificate can be mentioned in your CV for better shortlisting opportunity, because of its perceived importance by the visiting companies.*

Register at - https://docs.google.com/forms/d/13zNrZpGLpl_smkVmP670dsDDa60Amgg-ZeebKqwhayg/edit

Those who have successfully registered for all the events of the Soft Skill Program which will be hosted by Dr. Manu Vora, must have received the teams link over email. 

The first session is about Leadership Excellence and will be held on *25th March (8:30PM to 10:30PM).*

In this interactive session, Dr. Vora will discuss Leadership Excellence. You will learn various leadership characteristics. Difference between a manager and leader will be explored. You will examine your own leadership characteristics. Excellent leadership models will be discussed. He will sketch out a roadmap for leadership excellence and development. You will learn key concepts, best practices, and practical tools to enhance your leadership excellence.

*To avail the certificate, you will have to attend all the sessions. Your attendance and continuous presence during the session will be monitored by our team.*

6/5/22, 12:25 PM - Akshat Shah: Hello!

Researchers from *University of California, Berkeley*, invite you to participate in a *paid online study*. The purpose of the study is to better understand how people share or learn information online. 

Participation is in teams of two, so you need to find a teammate to participate with. The main study takes about 30 minutes, and each teammate will earn *Rs. 250* for participation. (So: Rs. 500 per team). 

During the study, you will see a series of news headlines taken from social media, and be asked some questions about them. Most of the questions are multiple choice, and have no “correct” answers per se – *we only want your opinion*. You may also have the option to share any interesting stories with your teammate. 

The study will be available from *06/06/2022* to *13/06/2022*, so if you and a friend/partner are interested, please find a date that works for both of you, and complete
 https://berkeley.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_5zQpnGUkCntV7GS

registration form. (Registration takes about 10 minutes). Both you and your teammate must register to participate.

More details about the study are available at this link - 

https://berkeley.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_5zQpnGUkCntV7GS
If you have any questions, please feel free to contact the study’s author(jimmy.narang@berkeley.edu), or any of the research assistants listed below - naidugarilokanath@gmail.com(Lokanath Naidugari)
19iamh01@uohyd.ac.in(Ananya Kumar)


Finally, feel free to share this information with other friends who might be interested in participating, but note that both members of the team must be a students of IIT BHU

Thankyou

8/28/22, 5:49 PM - Piyush: For all those not able to understand problem C of hacker cup:
The question wants to say that consider you have n strings, Now choose any sequence of dots and dashes in the universe. There should exist at most one way by which we can represent the sequence as concatenation of the n strings we have.(each of the n strings can be used any number of times (possibly zero or even infinite times).
Now you are given one string out of n strings and you need to output (n-1) strings such that the n strings together satisfies the above condition.

9/6/22, 1:42 PM - Pranav Suresh: A lot of you have been asking about the status of certain things that has to be done after the elections
These are the updates regarding the procedures and processes going on till now.

I am a member of the *Hostel and Welfare committee* in the parliament now. We have not been officially assigned the post now even though we have started our work unofficially considering the needs of the students.

*Regarding water coolers*: The tender for the maintenance of water coolers had to be reissued so the paper had been signed by the director today and maintenance work will start positively by this week itself.

*Mess refund*: It was getting delayed due to human errors in the document submitted to the CoW. The issue was because things were going digital but this cannot be changed now because it was done already. We are now cleaning up this mess by reverifing the docs daily going to the cow office to fasten up the process. But it will minimum take 20-25 days to complete the process .

*Waste and cows*: Talks are going on with NGOs and goshalas for the management of excess food from the hostels to manage waste and take away the cattle from the campus.

Along with that we are also working behind the conduction of *hostel elections.*

Discussions are also going on with proctors regarding the *campus security*. 

The committee was formed just a few days ago and these many jobs have already been done.

Me along with the students parliament will be there for all the needs of the students but please understand that all the things that has to be done will have to go through certain procedures which will take time. But we are pushing max from our end to speed up the process. So please be patient.

Also don't hesitate to inform your needs and concerns so that actions can be taken to ensure that.😇

Cine
Photography
Design
Outreach
Animation

10/19/22, 7:14 AM - Akshat Shah: *[IMPORTANT]*
*Senior Induction Mentor*
------------------------
*Form:* https://forms.gle/g8X9vdsaKXizQjL66
*Deadline: 11:59 AM, 19th October*
------------------------
Please fill out this form if you are interested in volunteering as a *Senior Induction Mentor* for the 
*Induction Mentor Program* - 2022 with Student Counselling Services. 

The new entrants are arriving on campus on *28th October*. To ensure that the upcoming batch gets comfortable with the college environment, we create Induction Mentor Groups. The Mentors are generally students from the *second year and above* who *guide the new entrants with the nitty-gritties of college life.*

It is a role of huge responsibility. Your interaction with the students defines their first impression of college and also thus has a great influence on the college culture. The engagements as an Induction Program include solving fundamental college-related doubts of mentees and taking weekly mentor group meets for the first few weeks.

As the authorities are not taking any crucial steps against any of these cases. We have opted for mass mailing for which we need you to mail the message to the ids mentioned below.
12/31/22, 5:59 PM - Aditya Kulkarni: To:director@itbhu.ac.in

CC:
office.proctor@itbhu.ac.in
security.parliament@itbhu.ac.in
vp.parliament@itbhu.ac.in
dosa@itbhu.ac.in

12/31/22, 5:59 PM - Aditya Kulkarni: Subject : Security of the students on the campus.
12/31/22, 5:59 PM - Aditya Kulkarni: Concerning the incidents happening on the campus in the last few months, the safety of students has become bigger issue. The number of cases of misbehaviour has increased. Recently, two students were walking on the road and a car passing by stopped. The person inside, started misbehaving with them, trying to pull them near the car. What if that person has managed to pull those students into the car? Why the outside cars are allowed to enter? Why not any action has been taken against such things? This is not the only case, there are dozens of similar incidents happening all over the campus and nothing has been done so far. We are on campus for almost 5 months and are constantly listening to such things. Is the administration taking any action against them? If yes, then why do these incidents repeat? 
Worst being, when we complain to the guards, they start moral policing and making statements as of why are we roaming outside at the time; sometimes they even start saying is this why your parents have sent you to the institute. Is this a right way to talk to the students? Many of us are Ph.D. scholars and have work in labs during night time and even the B.Tech and M.Tech students get time after evening hours due to their hectic class schedules. Are we supposed to tell these things to every guard on every corner? 
And when we ask for the solutions, the authorities in charge would enforce a curfew after 10 pm. Is this the only solution? We have even started to feel insecure at 6 pm. Would that mean, the authorities enforce a curfew after 6 pm? Is this the only way to make the campus secure? Why those people who misbehave with the students can’t be stopped?  
At last, we request you look into the matter and take appropriate actions to provide a safe and secure campus for the students.

Date - 14 Jan 2023.
Time - 2 PM -5 PM

1. DFS , BFS

6. Small to Large technique
